          <div class="card span6"><h3>Headers</h3><p class="card-desc">One header per line. Sensitive values are redacted in previews and reports by default.</p><textarea name="headersText" placeholder="Accept: application/json&#10;Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Cookies</h3><p class="card-desc">Use standard Cookie syntax or one name=value pair per line.</p><textarea name="cookiesText" placeholder="session=abc; theme=dark"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span12"><h3>Request body</h3><p class="card-desc">Body helpers apply to the standard HTTP engine. JavaScript browser mode performs GET navigation without a request body.</p><div class="field-grid"><div class="field s4"><label class="field-label">Body mode</label><select name="bodyMode" id="body-mode"><option value="none">None</option><option value="payload">Raw payload string</option><option value="json">JSON string</option><option value="json-file">JSON file simulation</option><option value="form">Form string</option><option value="form-file">Form file simulation</option><option value="payload-file">Payload file simulation</option><option value="binary-file">Binary file simulation</option><option value="multipart">Multipart fields</option></select></div><div class="field s8"><label class="field-label">Body content or multipart lines</label><textarea name="bodyText" placeholder='{&quot;username&quot;:&quot;test@example.com&quot;,&quot;password&quot;:&quot;change-me&quot;}'></textarea></div></div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="replay" class="panel">
        <div class="section-head"><div><h2>Replay and import</h2><p>Start from builder fields, raw HTTP/1.1, or a cURL command.</p></div><span class="section-tag">Input</span></div>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="card span4"><h3>Request source</h3><p class="card-desc">Choose which source becomes the base request.</p><div class="field"><label class="field-label">Mode</label><select name="requestMode" id="request-mode"><option value="builder">Builder fields</option><option value="raw">Raw HTTP request</option><option value="curl">cURL command</option></select></div><div class="field" style="margin-top:12px"><label class="field-label">Raw scheme</label><select name="rawScheme"><option>https</option><option>http</option></select></div></div>
          <div class="card span8"><h3>Raw HTTP/1.1 request</h3><textarea name="rawRequest" style="min-height:220px" placeholder="POST /api/login HTTP/1.1&#10;Host: example.com&#10;Content-Type: application/json&#10;&#10;{&quot;a&quot;:1}"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span12"><h3>Import from cURL</h3><textarea name="curlCommand" placeholder="curl 'https://example.com/api' -X POST -H 'Content-Type: application/json' --data-raw '{&quot;a&quot;:1}'"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Header file simulation</h3><textarea name="headersFileText" placeholder="User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0&#10;X-Bug-Bounty: H1-imr"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Cookie file simulation</h3><textarea name="cookiesFileText" placeholder="Cookie: session=abc; theme=dark"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span12"><h3>Load cookies alias</h3><textarea name="loadCookiesText" placeholder="session=abc&#10;csrf=token"></textarea><p class="help-text">Maps to <span class="mono">--load-cookies</span> and supports repeatable authenticated request flows.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="modifiers" class="panel">
        <div class="section-head"><div><h2>Modifiers and variables</h2><p>Apply deterministic changes after all imported request sources.</p></div><span class="section-tag">Transform</span></div>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Set headers</h3><textarea name="setHeaders" placeholder="Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}&#10;X-Test: 1"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Remove headers</h3><textarea name="removeHeaders" placeholder="X-Powered-By&#10;Server"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Set cookies</h3><textarea name="setCookies" placeholder="session={{SESSION}}&#10;theme=dark"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Remove cookies</h3><textarea name="removeCookies" placeholder="tracking_id"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Set query parameters</h3><textarea name="setQuery" placeholder="debug=true&#10;id=123"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Remove query parameters</h3><textarea name="removeQuery" placeholder="utm_source&#10;cachebuster"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Body replacements</h3><textarea name="replaceBody" placeholder="old=new&#10;guest=admin"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Template variables</h3><textarea name="variables" placeholder="BASE_URL=https://example.com&#10;TOKEN=abc123&#10;SESSION=s1"></textarea><div style="height:11px"></div><label class="field-label">Vars file simulation</label><textarea name="varsFileText" placeholder="USER_ID=1001"></textarea></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="browser-network" class="panel">
        <div class="section-head"><div><h2>Execution engine and network</h2><p>Use HTTP for exact request replay or Browser for JavaScript-rendered GET pages.</p></div><span class="section-tag">Engine</span></div>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="card accent span12"><h3>Execution engine</h3><p class="card-desc">Browser mode is optional and never crawls links. It navigates only to the configured URL.</p><div class="mode-switch"><label class="mode-option"><input type="radio" name="engineMode" value="http" checked><span class="mode-card"><strong>HTTP engine</strong><span>Python requests. Supports all current methods, bodies, raw replay, cURL import, proxy, reports, and cookie jars.</span></span></label><label class="mode-option"><input type="radio" name="engineMode" value="browser"><span class="mode-card"><strong>JavaScript browser</strong><span>Playwright-powered GET navigation. Captures the rendered DOM, final URL, console output, errors, cookies, and storage.</span></span></label></div></div>
          <div class="card span7 browser-only"><h3>Browser rendering</h3><p class="card-desc">These options are applied only when JavaScript browser mode is selected.</p><div class="field-grid"><div class="field s4"><label class="field-label">Browser engine</label><select name="browserEngine"><option value="chromium">Chromium</option><option value="firefox">Firefox</option><option value="webkit">WebKit</option></select></div><div class="field s4"><label class="field-label">Wait until</label><select name="browserWaitUntil"><option value="networkidle">Network idle</option><option value="load">Load</option><option value="domcontentloaded">DOM content loaded</option><option value="commit">Commit</option></select></div><div class="field s4"><label class="field-label">Viewport</label><input name="browserViewport" value="1366x768"></div><div class="field s6"><label class="field-label">Wait for CSS selector</label><input name="browserWaitSelector" placeholder="#app, .dashboard, [data-ready]"></div><div class="field s3"><label class="field-label">Extra wait (ms)</label><input name="browserWaitMs" type="number" min="0" max="600000" value="0"></div><div class="field s3"><label class="field-label">Executable path</label><input name="browserExecutable" placeholder="Optional"></div></div><div class="check-grid" style="margin-top:12px"><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="browserHeaded"> Show browser window</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="saveBrowserStorage"> Save updated storage state</label></div></div>
          <div class="card span5 browser-only"><h3>Browser storage state</h3><p class="card-desc">Paste Playwright storage-state JSON to preload cookies and local storage.</p><textarea name="browserStorageText" placeholder='{&quot;cookies&quot;:[],&quot;origins&quot;:[]}'></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span12"><h3>Network controls</h3><div class="field-grid"><div class="field s4"><label class="field-label">Timeout seconds</label><input name="timeout" type="number" min="0.1" step="0.1" value="30"></div><div class="field s8"><label class="field-label">Proxy</label><input name="proxy" placeholder="http://127.0.0.1:8080"></div></div><div class="check-grid" style="margin-top:12px"><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="noRedirects"> Do not follow redirects (HTTP only)</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="showRedirectChain" checked> Show redirect chain</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="insecure"> Disable TLS verification</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="noEnvProxy" checked> Ignore environment proxy</label></div></div>
          <div class="notice browser-only"><strong>Browser-mode limitation:</strong> JavaScript rendering is intentionally limited to one GET page navigation. For POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, bodies, or multipart data, keep the HTTP engine selected.</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="output" class="panel">
        <div class="section-head"><div><h2>Output, reports and evidence</h2><p>Control visibility and save reproducible execution artifacts.</p></div><span class="section-tag">Artifacts</span></div>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="card span12"><h3>Execution and exports</h3><div class="check-grid"><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="include"> Include response headers</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="showRequest" checked> Show prepared request</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="dryRun"> Dry-run</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="rawOutput"> Raw output</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="exportCurl" checked> Export cURL</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="exportPython"> Export Python</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="savePreparedRequest"> Save prepared request</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="saveOutput"> Save response/rendered DOM</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="saveCookies"> Save cookies</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="cookieJar"> Use cookie jar</label></div></div>
          <div class="card span7"><h3>Reports and session evidence</h3><div class="check-grid"><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="reportJson" checked> JSON report</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="reportHtml" checked> HTML report</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="saveSession"> Save session directory</label><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="noRedactReports"> Disable report redaction</label></div><p class="help-text">Browser reports include page title, console messages, page errors, rendered DOM size, cookies, lifecycle wait settings, and storage state metadata.</p></div>
          <div class="card span5"><h3>Cookie jar seed</h3><textarea name="cookieJarText" placeholder="session=abc"></textarea></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Configuration</h3><label class="field-label">Config path</label><input name="configPath" placeholder="/path/to/forgrequest.config"><div style="height:11px"></div><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" name="initConfig"> Generate sample config artifact</label></div>
          <div class="card span6"><h3>Execution controls</h3><p class="card-desc">The single primary Run request button remains in the upper-right corner next to the version.</p><div class="actions"><button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" id="dry-btn">Preview dry-run</button><button type="reset" class="btn btn-danger">Reset form</button></div></div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </form>

    <section id="diff" class="panel"><div class="section-head"><div><h2>Response diff</h2><p>Compare two saved responses or arbitrary text without sending a request.</p></div><span class="section-tag">Local</span></div><div class="card"><div class="diff-grid"><textarea id="diff-left" placeholder="Left response"></textarea><textarea id="diff-right" placeholder="Right response"></textarea></div><div class="actions" style="margin-top:12px"><button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="diff-btn">Run diff</button><label class="check"><input type="checkbox" id="diff-nobody"> Summary only</label></div></div></section>

    <section id="help" class="panel"><div class="section-head"><div><h2>Feature map</h2><p>Web coverage and execution boundaries.</p></div><span class="section-tag">Reference</span></div><div class="feature-list"><div class="feature"><strong>Request construction</strong><span>Methods, URL, headers, cookies, query changes, body helpers, variables, raw requests, and cURL import.</span></div><div class="feature"><strong>JavaScript rendering</strong><span>Single-page Playwright navigation with Chromium, Firefox, or WebKit; rendered DOM and browser events.</span></div><div class="feature"><strong>Session context</strong><span>Cookie files, cookie jars, browser storage-state import/export, and report redaction.</span></div><div class="feature"><strong>Evidence</strong><span>Prepared raw request, cURL, Python reproduction, response body, rendered DOM, JSON/HTML reports, and session folders.</span></div><div class="feature"><strong>Network</strong><span>Timeout, redirects, proxy, TLS verification, and environment-proxy controls.</span></div><div class="feature"><strong>Boundaries</strong><span>No crawler, scanner, automated discovery, link traversal, or vulnerability classification.</span></div></div><div class="notice" style="margin-top:13px">Keep the Web Console bound to <span class="mono">127.0.0.1</span>. It can send requests and launch a browser on behalf of the local operator.</div></section>

    <section class="terminal" id="output-console"><div class="terminal-bar"><div class="terminal-title"><span class="dots"><span class="dot"></span><span class="dot"></span><span class="dot"></span></span>Execution console</div><div class="run-status" id="run-status">ready</div></div><pre id="output">Configure a request and use Run request. The generated command, stdout, stderr, browser events, and artifact links will appear here.</pre><div class="artifacts" id="artifacts"></div></section>
  </main>
</div>
<script>
const $=(s,r=document)=>r.querySelector(s);const $$=(s,r=document)=>Array.from(r.querySelectorAll(s));
const form=$('#request-form');
function activatePanel(id){$$('.tab').forEach(b=>b.classList.toggle('active',b.dataset.panel===id));$$('.panel').forEach(p=>p.classList.toggle('active',p.id===id));}
$$('.tab').forEach(btn=>btn.addEventListener('click',()=>activatePanel(btn.dataset.panel)));
